-- Branson May Start Microfinance Fund for U.K., The Times Reports
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2011-12-17T13:51:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-17/branson-may-start-microfinance-fund-for-u-k-the-times-reports.html
Virgin Group Ltd. Chairman  Richard Branson  is considering setting up a fund to make small loans to
entrepreneurs in the U.K.,  The Times  reported, citing an
interview.  The fund would be similar to so-called microfinance funds
operating in India and Africa, Branson was cited as saying.  He also recommended employees working fewer hours and
sharing their jobs as a means of reducing unemployment in the
U.K., and said he will discuss his proposals with Prime Minister
David Cameron, the London-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
